			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&message.id=142625#M142625">7</a> of 59
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1352 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><BR>Ok, part I discussed the concept of level segragation in general, and outlined some of the advantages and disadvantages. Now lets look at the specifics.&nbsp; Bear in mind, this is hardly a perfect proposal; I'm sure I've overlooked things, and frankly, some of the choices I've had to make are less than optimal because there is no "perfect" choice. In general, I tried to stick to four tiers.&nbsp; After much struggle, I had to give up and go to five, as the game just falls into definate eras--possibly when the design teams changed?&nbsp; Anyway, these are hardly ironclad proposals; exact levels, AA, tradeskills would be up to Sony and could be tweaked as needed.</DIV>
<DIV>Generally, each tier overlaps the next somewhat so players could jump early &amp; get powerleveled if their sole interest was just getting a character up to raiding level.&nbsp; Also, the lower tiers don't even have all the zones in the game; there's little or no point to putting Vex Thal on a newbie server, so this means the lower tier servers require less hardware.&nbsp; Higher tier servers DO include all the lower tier zones (due to quests, etc.), and all the zones are identical across all servers (except for the zone-out to missing zones, of course).</DIV>
<DIV>Note: upward transfers are free.&nbsp; Lateral transfers (within a tier) still cost $75!</DIV>
<DIV><BR><FONT color=#ffff00>Tier I Servers: Lvl 1-25. Tradeskills limited to 100. </FONT><BR>Old World: All minus Lguk, Sol A&amp;B, Permafrost, CT, The Hole, and old planes. <BR>Kunark: None but Cablis E&amp;W, FOB, Kurns, and LOIO. (POK book is only way here)<BR>Velious: None.<BR>Luclin: only Shar Vahl, Bazaar, Hollowshade, Shadeweaver, PC, Nexus, Shadow Haven, Netherbian Lair, Marus Seru.<BR>LOY: None.<BR>LDON: None.<BR>GOD: None.<BR>OOW: None.<BR>Free zones: Shadowrest, Stonebrunt.<BR>POP: only POKnowledge to stitch it all together.</DIV>
<DIV>The emphasis here is on learning the game/class, questing, etc.&nbsp; "Endgame" content would be Upper Guk, Blackburrow (bottom), Unrest, and Najena. </DIV>
<DIV><BR><FONT color=#ffff00>Tier II Servers: Lvl 18-50. Tradeskills limited to 200.</FONT><BR>Old World: All except maybe the Hole and the planes. (optional: include old planes)<BR>Kunark: All except Chardok, HS, Seb, and VP. <BR>Velious: from Iceclad through Great Divide. (no Kael, VL, ST).<BR>Luclin: all except ME, AC, AR, GE, Grey, Ssra, VT (IOW, the 50+ zones)<BR>Add LDON.<BR>Add LOY.<BR>Add Nederia's Landing &amp; Jaggedpine<BR>Emphasis here is on more leveling, quests, learning difficult dungeons, and beginning raids. "Endgame" content would be Sol B, Perma, Nurga, Droga, Dalnir, COM.</DIV>
<DIV><BR><FONT color=#ffff00>Tier III Servers: Level 40-60 (w/20AA). Old tradeskill limit of 1 @250.</FONT><BR>All zones through Luclin + LDON + old planes.<BR>POP still not included!&nbsp; (optionally, add POT and first four planes but I don't like that)<BR>Emphasis here is on gearing up and climbing into the early planes; serious "old-time" raiding, epic 1.0.&nbsp; "Endgame content" would be Luclin and the old planes.</DIV>
<DIV><BR><FONT color=#ffff00>Tier IV Servers: 55-65 (w/300 AA).</FONT><BR>All zones through POP + LDON (and maybe GOD, though I lean against that)<BR>Emphasis here is on the "huge raid" phase of the game.&nbsp; This tier might actually have fewer servers than Tier III, in order to maintain 'critical mass'necessary to generate raids. "Endgame" content is Elementals/POTime.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Tier V Servers: unlimited.&nbsp; OOW and all future expansions.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Ok folks, there it is, now finish shredding it. :-)</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<font color="white"><font size=1>S-Girl said: After casting 8 rounds of KEI I had a grand total of... 300pp. I was shocked. She'd told me she was broke and I'd just laughed, but seeing the donations for 4hrs of mana regen was simply... well it was a joke. <br>I left her logged on for about 1.5 hrs and in all that time had lfg up (to see if it was really as bad as she'd said) and I got a total of 0 tells for a group - but about 50 for KEI</font></font>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
