<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&message.id=142630#M142630">9</a> of 59
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1323 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>No.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I've stayed out of these threads up to now, but NO just NO NO NO NO NO NO.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It fixes a short term need with a horrible community breaking &lt;deletes out the part about insanely stupid&gt; game destroying artificial convention.&nbsp; Is sort of a self-perpuating welfare system.... start out poor and stay poor unless you already have a character above 60 or whatever.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally, I don't need bazaar gear to start out my young characters.&nbsp; You might say it would be an advantage for everyone to learn to play their characters "as designed" but how many people are going to be willing/able to start out without a magic weapon below 20?&nbsp; It is entirely possible to do so, but how long exactly do you think a level 20 enchanter for example to pay for all of their spells?&nbsp; With all the low levels concentrated in a small area the competition for cash mobs would be horrendous.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ok, let's talk community for a second.&nbsp; This would absolutely destroy the making and keeping of friends.&nbsp; And you have to realize that any trransfer levels are going to be completely arbitrary.&nbsp; Say it is every 20 levels.... that means a 22 and a 19 would be split.&nbsp; A 39 and a 45.&nbsp; A 59 and a 61.... How well do you think that will actually work?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Do you really think the general population base is willing to say good bye to temp?&nbsp; Or no kei until you get to the level 60 server?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It also destroys the need for reputation and integrity.&nbsp; Oh boy!&nbsp; I can wear out my welcome on 5 servers instead of just one!&nbsp; I can grief all I want at 19 because at 20 I am going somewhere else.&nbsp; There I can do horrible awful things from 30 to 39 because at 40 I get a "get out of jail card free".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Please explain to ME how I want to be on a world where everybody is essentially the same level?&nbsp; What kind of world is that?&nbsp; WHY would I want it?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>How is this going to work from a technical standpoint for log in?&nbsp; Umm... let's see... I'll pull up the 30 world select screen.&nbsp; Uh no, I forgot I dinged last nigh before going to bed.&nbsp; Now, what server is this alt on?&nbsp; Umm... I have 8 characters scattered about that I can't see and I want to check out if Evil Erudites start out speaking Old Erudian.&nbsp; Hmm.. I can't go to another server and make a character to find out.&nbsp; Oh well, I guess I can look it up instead of finding out for myself in 3 minutes....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Are you willing to pay for additional people/equipment?&nbsp; Can't see how something like this is going to be able to happen without additional cost.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I could go on and on about the deficits of such a system.&nbsp; I won't.&nbsp; I can feel my blood pressure beginning to rise.&nbsp; Just THINK about this.&nbsp; Think it through.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Honestly, other than losing my friends more often than I do now, it wouldn't really impact my style of play much.&nbsp; However, I think it would be extremely detrimental to the game in the long run.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
