		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Nolrog:&nbsp; Backwards moves not permitted.&nbsp; Sorry, I didn't specify that, but it was meant by design.&nbsp; If you want to be a level 1 on a Tier V server, sac away....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Everyone else: No matter what solution is adopted to the game's problems, there will be significant downsides.&nbsp; The alternative is to do nothing and watch the game die.&nbsp; Sony is going to have to do something, and whatever it is, a bunch of people aren't going to like it.&nbsp; Braxis suggested, and I developed, what I think is a solution to MANY longstanding problems.&nbsp; It will create some of its own, and I figure there will be six months to a year of tracking down broken quests that low and mid-tier servers suddenly can't complete.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, players in a guild get split up, but you can found seperate chapters and still be in the same guild.&nbsp; You just can't group until the lower player&nbsp;levels enough; note that the levels are designed to overlap a lot, in part to help with this and in part to speed advancment for the "high level at all costs" types.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The "split up" will eventually cure itself as the lower level payers advance.&nbsp; And having endured three major exoduses (exodii?) as the guild I founded advanced "too fast" or "too slow" for some, thats a split thats going to happen to almost all guilds anyway.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another major benefit is that now the low and high level communities (which for the most part are actually the same players on different characters) can now be discerned and their needs more easily identified.&nbsp;&nbsp; But the A#1 benefit is to raise the population density, so people can find groups &amp; raid content that is largely being abandoned.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<font color="white"><font size=1>S-Girl said: After casting 8 rounds of KEI I had a grand total of... 300pp. I was shocked. She'd told me she was broke and I'd just laughed, but seeing the donations for 4hrs of mana regen was simply... well it was a joke. <br>I left her logged on for about 1.5 hrs and in all that time had lfg up (to see if it was really as bad as she'd said) and I got a total of 0 tells for a group - but about 50 for KEI</font></font>
							</div>
								
