			>
			<DIV></DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Ice, the person who hasn't thought about it is <EM>you</EM>. Allow me to address your points.....</FONT><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Iceblossom wrote:<BR>
<DIV>No.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I've stayed out of these threads up to now, but NO just NO NO NO NO NO NO.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It fixes a short term need with a horrible community breaking game destroying artificial convention.&nbsp; Is sort of a self-perpuating welfare system.... start out poor and stay poor unless you already have a character above 60 or whatever.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>On this one, I have to be a bit sarcastic.&nbsp; I certainly managed to level up that way, as did the ENTIRE original generation of players.&nbsp; Are you arguing it's not even possible to level up without help? How lame.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally, I don't need bazaar gear to start out my young characters.&nbsp; You might say it would be an advantage for everyone to learn to play their characters "as designed" but how many people are going to be willing/able to start out without a magic weapon below 20?&nbsp; It is entirely possible to do so, but how long exactly do you think a level 20 enchanter for example to pay for all of their spells?&nbsp; With all the low levels concentrated in a small area the competition for cash mobs would be horrendous.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Ok, sorry you're just not an old school player.&nbsp; I did it, and I didn't have sugar daddy standing over me.&nbsp; I thought I was awsome hot stuff when a lvl 40 gave me a (non magical) shan'tok.&nbsp; A whopping Dam 8, at sixth level.&nbsp; Woohoo!</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ok, let's talk community for a second.&nbsp; This would absolutely destroy the making and keeping of friends.&nbsp; And you have to realize that any trransfer levels are going to be completely arbitrary.&nbsp; Say it is every 20 levels.... that means a 22 and a 19 would be split.&nbsp; A 39 and a 45.&nbsp; A 59 and a 61.... How well do you think that will actually work?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>How does it destroy community and the keeping of friends? You can follow them from server to server.&nbsp; If you level THAT much slower than your friends (or they than you) you're going to get split up <EM>anyway</EM>.&nbsp; And obviously, you started your rant before I even finished posting the idea, since you didn't see the overlap.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Do you really think the general population base is willing to say good bye to temp?&nbsp; Or no kei until you get to the level 60 server?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The population base wasn't willing to give up KEI &amp; Virt&nbsp;under level 45, but when Sony restricted it, they did.&nbsp; And again, you jumped the gun without seeing how the levels broke down.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It also destroys the need for reputation and integrity.&nbsp; Oh boy!&nbsp; I can wear out my welcome on 5 servers instead of just one!&nbsp; I can grief all I want at 19 because at 20 I am going somewhere else.&nbsp; There I can do horrible awful things from 30 to 39 because at 40 I get a "get out of jail card free".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Some of the players on your new server came from your old server.&nbsp; If not, they still have guildmates and&nbsp;friends there.&nbsp; Your rep WILL follow you.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Please explain to ME how I want to be on a world where everybody is essentially the same level?&nbsp; What kind of world is that?&nbsp; WHY would I want it?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>In the long run, my question isn't whether you would want it, but whether the game will need it to survive and prosper.&nbsp; From the tenor of your questions, I would gather that "game balance" is not a part of your lexicon.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>How is this going to work from a technical standpoint for log in?&nbsp; Umm... let's</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>If you read the proposal, you'd know a /movelog command is required to change servers.&nbsp; And that you can voluntarily CHOOSE to stay with friends at lower level by not executing it.... your xp is capped.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>see... I'll pull up the 30 world select screen.&nbsp; Uh no, I forgot I dinged last nigh before going to bed.&nbsp; Now, what server is this alt on?&nbsp; Umm... I have 8 characters</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>You are on whatever server you chose to be on.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>scattered about that I can't see and I want to check out if Evil Erudites start out speaking Old Erudian.&nbsp; Hmm.. I can't go to another server and make a character to find out.&nbsp; Oh well, I guess I can look it up instead of finding out for myself in 3 minutes....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>So what you're saying is you have somehow managed to fill up all 8 slots on EVERY Tier 1 server?&nbsp; You have some serious misconceptions here.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Are you willing to pay for additional people/equipment?&nbsp; Can't see how something like this is going to be able to happen without additional cost.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The additional cost is only in the setup and redesign.&nbsp; In the end, the maintenance cost is LESS, because the lower tier servers don't have the same number of zones as the high tier servers; therefore while the total number of servers (across all levels) may be the same, the actual hardware requirements are LESS.&nbsp; The major problem would be with the "special ruleset" servers; though I'd have no problem with exempting them from the level limits, or even having ONE server that has a special ruleset of "all levels play together."</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I could go on and on about the deficits of such a system.&nbsp; I won't.&nbsp; I can feel my blood pressure beginning to rise.&nbsp; Just THINK about this.&nbsp; Think it through.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Obviously you haven't.&nbsp; Take aspirin for the blood pressure.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Honestly, other than losing my friends more often than I do now, it wouldn't really impact my style of play much.&nbsp; However, I think it would be extremely detrimental to the game in the long run.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>It's fair to say that we do not agree on what is detrimental.&nbsp; I think the continued decline of the game as it exists is far more dangerous to its long term survival.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
