<HR>
Elizor-LS wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>On this one, I have to be a bit sarcastic.&nbsp; I certainly managed to level up that way, as did the ENTIRE original generation of players.&nbsp; Are you arguing it's not even possible to level up without help? How lame.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff>No. She's saying there's people who DON"T want to level up unless they can twink. Not everyone likes to play starting from scratch. I certainly don't, and many of my friends don't. </FONT></DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Ok, sorry you're just not an old school player.&nbsp; I did it, and I didn't have sugar daddy standing over me.&nbsp; I thought I was awsome hot stuff when a lvl 40 gave me a (non magical) shan'tok.&nbsp; A whopping Dam 8, at sixth level.&nbsp; Woohoo!</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff>Actually, Ice has been around a long time. She has rarely ever twinked her toons, or loaned them money. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff>Again, not everyone wants to play each toon from scratch. Some people actually enjoy twinking toons and giving them money to afford stuff</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>How does it destroy community and the keeping of friends? You can follow them from server to server.&nbsp; If you level THAT much slower than your friends (or they than you) you're going to get split up <EM>anyway</EM>.&nbsp; And obviously, you started your rant before I even finished posting the idea, since you didn't see the overlap.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#0033ff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3366ff>It' splits people up. That's how it destroy's a community. Yea, after a certain level difference people can't group together. It doesn't mean they still can't interact with each other. If you have different levels on different servers like you're suggesting, that other type of interaction would be impossible. I made many friends as a 65 necro, with people I couldn't group with. Doesn't mean I didn't hang out with them and talk with them though. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The population base wasn't willing to give up KEI &amp; Virt&nbsp;under level 45, but when Sony restricted it, they did.&nbsp; And again, you jumped the gun without seeing how the levels broke down.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff>Yes, and what you're suggesting is far worse than giving up KEI and Virt. Split the servers by level and you'll have people leaving in droves. </FONT>".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Some of the players on your new server came from your old server.&nbsp; If not, they still have guildmates and&nbsp;friends there.&nbsp; Your rep WILL follow you.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff>It may follow you, but it won't have as big an impact as it does today. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>In the long run, my question isn't whether you would want it, but whether the game will need it to survive and prosper.&nbsp; From the tenor of your questions, I would gather that "game balance" is not a part of your lexicon.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#3333ff>That's the thing. The game DOESNT need it to survive. EQ survived 5 years without a server set up like this, it'll survive another 5 without it. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
