		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Remember that not all guilds are progression-oriented. Take a small guild (10-12 regulars ranging from level&nbsp;46-65) who enjoy hanging out and chatting&nbsp;in the lower tier planes just for fun, and don't really do much else. Take away their ability to do what they enjoy by splitting them across servers, and I can guarantee a number of them would leave the game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But like I said before, if you're looking at it only from a progression standpoint, it's a pretty good idea. People with other views might see it as a terrible idea.</DIV>
