			>
			<DIV>Okay, I have stopped and taken the time to review both of your messages, the general one and the message of specifics and I still am not in favor of such a move.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Look at it from the perspective of my level 43 shaman.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I am UBER to the new&nbsp;players coming up in the world.&nbsp; I have the opportunity to help them when I can, advise them when its appropriate and generally be a big brother to those that do not know better.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I am still young enough to be a "whipper snapper" to those level 65+ players.&nbsp; They help me when they can, advise me when its appropriate&nbsp;and generally are my big brothers and sisters because I don't know better.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Your suggestion reminds me of the book, "It Takes a Village to Raise a Child."&nbsp; Your suggestion takes the village out of the game allowing each player to basically raise themselves; Alah "Lord of the Flies."&nbsp; Thinking of my own kids, I can only shudder at the thought.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sorry, I would not want to live in such a world much less play in one!</DIV>
