		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I myself have mixed feelings about this. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>First question:&nbsp; Will you still be able to do cross server chat? I believe if so this will allow you to keep your friends list.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Over all I really like the idea.&nbsp; Myself I get frustrated at seeing noobies running around in better equip than myself and other old timers.&nbsp; I feel that when EQ was first designed if was for each person to be out earning there own gear.&nbsp; When Bazarr came I had the hopes that it would be used to sell trade items, spells, and the like. But sadly enough that is far from the case. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I suppose I'm just a true old timer and always will be. If you can't get it yourself, where is the fun in it.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>Over the four years I've played, LOTS of changes have came about.&nbsp; The one I keep waiting for is all equipment to be made NO DROP.&nbsp; Then what you have you can honestly say is yours and not bought.&nbsp; This wouldn't eliminate the share account, it could still be used for cash, spells, and trade skill items.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just my 2cp worth.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I don't expect to see any drastic changes made soon though.&nbsp; Most likely if something is done, only the high end players will benefit. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kat</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
