<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&message.id=142668#M142668">23</a> of 59
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1215 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I do admire the OP's passion for the game for posting such an audacious idea. But I simply will not support any form of level-based server segregation for reasons so clearly written by previous posters. In my opinion it would create far more problems than it "solves".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Allow me to share my experience last night...&nbsp;I was in a upper-50's group in Harbingers' Spire. It was the&nbsp;first time a few of us, myself included, had set foot inside OoW. After getting our feet wet with the first two rooms and experienced some minor difficulty, a L70 druid/chanter duo graciously, and without asking,&nbsp;showed us the ropes. They buffed us,&nbsp;single-pulled nameds until we got the pathing and aggro ranges down, and even offered to escort us deeper into the zone for more challenging content except our party was breaking up for the night. A great experience all around.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I don't recall offhand if the OP's level limits would permit those L70's on the same server as my 55 rogue. I do know that my&nbsp;L56 druid would no longer be able to drive-by buff people in the newbie zones. I feel that this type of benevolence from higher-level players is greatly appreciated far more often than not,&nbsp;and would be dearly missed if level-based server segregation ever came into being.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There are a few valid reasons to arbitrarily separate players into different servers... non-consensual PvP in various flavors, roleplay preferred, testing, non-English speaking... but levels? Nuh uh.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>12-22-2004</span> <span class=time_text>10:58 AM</span>
		</span>
